organization.fullName: Chia Tai Tianqing Pharmaceutical Group Co., Ltd.

identificationModule.briefTitle: TQC2731 Clinical Trial for the Treatment of Severe Asthma With Injection
identificationModule.officialTitle: A Multicenter, Randomized, Double-blind, Placebo-Controlled Phase III Clinical Trial to Evaluate the Efficacy and Safety of TQC2731 Injections in Patients With Poorly Controlled Severe Asthma

leadSponsor.name: Shanghai Chia Tai Tianqing Pharmaceutical Technology Development Co., Ltd.

descriptionModule.briefSummary: This study is a multicenter, randomized, double-blind, parallel-group, placebo-controlled Phase III clinical trial designed to evaluate the efficacy and safety of TQC2731 injection (420 mg Q4W) in adult subjects with inadequately controlled severe asthma. A total of 660 subjects are expected to be enrolled, with subjects randomized in a 1:1 ratio to receive either TQC2731 (420 mg Q4W) or placebo (Q4W) via subcutaneous (SC) administration.

armGroups.label: TQC2731 injection
armGroups.description: TQC2731 injection, 4 weeks as a treatment cycle. Study drug administration from Day 0 up to Week 48.

armGroups.label: Placebo
armGroups.description: Placebo,4 weeks as a treatment cycle.Study drug administration from Day 0 up to Week 48.

interventions.name: TQC2731 injection
interventions.description: TQC2731 injection can specifically bind to the Thymic Stromal Lymphopoietin (TSLP) protein, blocking TSLP-dependent downstream signaling expression in engineered cells and inhibiting the production of inflammatory cytokines.

primaryOutcomes.description: Annualized incidence of asthma exacerbations (AAER) during the 52-week treatment period.
primaryOutcomes.timeFrame: From the first day of dosing to the completion of 52 weeks of treatment

secondaryOutcomes.measure: The change in forced expiratory volume in 1 second (FEV1)
secondaryOutcomes.description: At Week 52, the change from baseline in forced expiratory volume in 1 second (FEV1) prior to dosing and before the use of a bronchodilator (pre-BD administration).
secondaryOutcomes.timeFrame: Week 52 before dosing and before the use of bronchodilators (pre-Bronchodilator (pre-BD) administration)

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Change in total score of standardized asthma quality of life questionnaire
secondaryOutcomes.description: Change from baseline in standardized asthma quality of life questionnaire (AQLQ(S)+12) total score at week 52. Scores above 5 points indicate a relatively good quality of life, while scores below 3 points suggest a relatively poor quality of life.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Change in Asthma Control Questionnaire-6 (ACQ-6) score
secondaryOutcomes.description: Mean change from baseline in weekly mean asthma symptom diary score at week 52, , The higher the score, the more severe the asthma symptoms.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Mean change in weekly mean asthma symptom diary score
secondaryOutcomes.description: Mean change from baseline in weekly mean asthma symptom diary score at week 52

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Change in European Quality of Life 5 Dimensions 5 Level (EQ-5D-5L) Questionnaire score
secondaryOutcomes.description: Change from baseline in European Quality of Life 5 Dimensions 5 Level (EQ-5D-5L) Questionnaire score at Week 52, a higher score indicates a better quality of life.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Change in mean rescue medication use, average peak expiratory flow rate (PEF) in the morning and night
secondaryOutcomes.description: Change from baseline in the average weekly dose of rescue medication and the average peak expiratory flow rate (PEF) per week in the morning and night, respectively

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Changes in exhaled nitric oxide Fractional exhaled nitric oxide (FENO) (ppb), peripheral blood eosinophils, total serum Immunoglobulin E (IgE).
secondaryOutcomes.description: Change from baseline in exhaled nitric oxide FENO (ppb) at week 52.
Change from baseline in peripheral blood eosinophils at week 52.
Change from baseline in total serum IgE at week 52.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Proportion of subjects with ≥1 asthma exacerbation
secondaryOutcomes.description: Proportion of subjects with ≥1 asthma exacerbation

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Number of days of glucocorticoid use due to acute exacerbations
secondaryOutcomes.description: Number of days of glucocorticoid use due to acute exacerbations

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Average amount of hormone used per acute exacerbation (prednisone equivalent)
secondaryOutcomes.description: Average amount of hormone used per acute exacerbation (prednisone equivalent)

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Incidence of anti-drug antibodies (ADAs) in subjects
secondaryOutcomes.description: Immunogenicity: Incidence of anti-drug antibodies (ADAs) in subjects and their titers.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Incidence of neutralizing antibodies(NAB) in subjects
